<subSubSection pageId="34" pageNumber="35" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="34.[151,1437,152,359]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,225,251]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Etymology.</emphasis>
The Latin name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jordal and Smith" authorityYear="2020" box="[530,664,225,251]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Scolytodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bombycinus">
<emphasis box="[530,664,225,251]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">bombycinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a masculine nominative adjective, meaning silky, referring to the very smooth, thin and long setae in the female frons.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
